verbose_text: With mitochondrial complex IV subunits I (COXI) and III (COXIII) as markers, only re-expression of mouse WT C1qbp rescued the amount of complex IV protein (XREF_FIG A, upper panel, lane 3), confirming causality between loss of C1QBP and diminished levels of OXPHOS subunits.
